sql:
SELECT player_id, points_per_game
FROM season_stats
WHERE points_per_game = (SELECT MAX(points_per_game) FROM season_stats);

external_knowledge:
- Performance refers to the overall contribution of a player to their team, considering various statistics like points, rebounds, assists, etc.; 
- Team standings imply the ranking of teams based on their total scores and games played, serving as context for individual player performance; 
- User roles are considered to potentially filter access to sensitive player information.

sql:
SELECT AVG(points_per_game) AS average_points_per_game
FROM season_stats
WHERE games_played > 40;
